CJSC '''AccessBank Tajikistan''' is a mid-size bank in [[Tajikistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/business/2504976.html|title=Int’l financial institutions to continue supporting AccessBank – Fitch|date=10 March 2016|work=Trend.Az}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.trend.az/azerbaijan/other/2435838.html|title=Fitch affirms AccessBank’s credit rating at investment grade level|date=21 September 2015|work=Trend.Az}}</ref>  The bank is currently led by chairman Katharina Sсhaсhtner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theworldfolio.com/interviews/accessing-opportunity/3362/|title=Tajikistan - Katharina Schachtner, General Manager of AccessBank|author=The Worldfolio|publisher=}}</ref>

AccessBank is 100% foreign-owned, including shareholders Access Microfinance Holding AG (63.429%), [http://www.ebrd.com European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD)] – (13.714%), [http://www.ifc.org International Finance Cooperation (IFC)] – (13.714%), & [https://www.kfw.de/kfw.de-2.html KfW Development Bank] – (9.143%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accessbank.tj/en/about/history/|title=History |publisher=AccessBank Tajikistan}}</ref>

