[[File:Global Center for Health Innovation.jpg|thumb|right|The building nearing completion in 2013]]
The '''Global Center for Health Innovation''',<ref name=pd2013>{{cite news |first=Karen |last=Farkas |title=Medical Mart in Cleveland Now Named the Global Center for Health Innovation |url=http://www.cleveland.com/cuyahoga-county/index.ssf/2013/02/medical_mart_in_cleveland_now.html |work=[[The Plain Dealer]] |date=2013-02-19 |accessdate=2013-02-20 }}</ref> also known as the '''Medical Mart''', is a $465 million [[joint venture]] by [[Cuyahoga County, Ohio|Cuyahoga County]] and [[Vornado Realty Trust#Merchandise Mart Properties, Inc. (MMPI)|MMPI]] to construct a permanent showroom of medical, surgical and hospital goods along with a new [[Huntington Convention Center of Cleveland]] in [[Downtown Cleveland|downtown]] [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Laura |last=Johnston |title=Rain Hasn't Slowed Med Mart Construction |url=http://www.cleveland.com/medicalmart/index.ssf/2011/05/rain_hasnt_slowed_med_mart_con.html |work=The Plain Dealer |date=2011-05-19 |accessdate=2013-02-20 }}</ref> Construction of the project, which is largely being funded by a 0.25% sales tax increase passed by Cuyahoga County commissioners in 2007, began in May 2011. {{As of|February 2013}}, construction of the joint Medical Mart-Cleveland Convention Center is well underway on the historic [[The Mall (Cleveland)|Mall]].<ref name=pd2013/>The Medical Mart concept is modeled after that of the [[Merchandise Mart]] in [[Chicago]], and will be managed by MMPI, the same company that operates the Merchandise Mart.

The center is attached to the [[Hilton Cleveland Downtown Hotel]].
