{{Expand Polish|date=October 2014}} '''Surangel S. Whipps''' is a [[Palau]]an businessman and [[politician]]. He served as the president of the [[Senate of Palau]] from 2007 to 2009, and as the speaker of the [[House of Delegates of Palau]] from 1993 to 1996.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.palauoek.net/senate/SenatorWhipps.asp |title=Biography on senate website |accessdate=2008-11-05 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724001450/http://www.palauoek.net/senate/SenatorWhipps.asp |archivedate=July 24, 2011 |df= }}</ref> He is from [[Airai]]. His net worth as of January 2018 is around $450 million US dollars.
He graduated from [[University of Baltimore]] in 1971 and returned to Palau in 1972.
==Politics== In January 2008, Whipps proposed a bill requiring the [[minimum wage]] to apply not just to Palauans, but to non-resident workers as well. It was reasoned that this would help more Palauans to become employed, due to the increased cost of hiring non-resident workers.<ref name=ngelekelbelau>[http://ngelekelbelau.blogspot.com.au/2008/02/should-non-resident-workers-be-granted.html "Should non-resident workers be granted minimum wage?"], nGelEkeL BeLau, 5 February 2008.</ref>
